<subSubSection id="1EF2BD4BC8474C08D513328655CF566D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="CB0B5742D4C399AE1AB227E1B5139E24" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="DDE866D829646EF2C15561ED3117FB04" LSID="562BDB18-117F-5B91-85EB-98955E24FD7E" authority="Tabacaru, 1980" authorityName="Tabacaru" authorityYear="1980" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Banatodesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Banatodesmus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Banatodesmus Tabacaru, 1980</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="65EA52A6DAF396DBC28C5393D84C815A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type species">
<paragraph id="01230F7EA2C78A91829ED85B4E28E6DD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EB77F4D745058C927F9059D30E12562F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="29E5F4C09FB4FC35113263AFA6DB2CCD" authorityName="Tabacaru" authorityYear="1980" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Trichopolydesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trichopolydesmus (Banatodesmus) jeanneli" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jeanneli" subGenus="Banatodesmus">Trichopolydesmus (Banatodesmus) jeanneli</taxonomicName>
Tabacaru, 1980, by monotypy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0FA83F0443E031502AA6B084A0B685B8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="739047AB8B6E87F63C1350F34CFBBBC7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="60DAA92D3A45241F058669D1F66AF619" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Different from other European 
<taxonomicName id="C64C23217B388A8217129671CDC04D35" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1910" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Trichopolydesmidae</taxonomicName>
by the presence of an enlarged, oval, paddle-like solenomere (s in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1E956BFC85559AD94DCC16EB09844488" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Banatodesmus jeanneli (Tabacaru, 1980), ♂ from Pestera Haiducească de la Moldova Nouă Cave, Romania, left gonopod (NHMW MY 10257) A mesal view B antero-distal view C distal view D posterior view E anterior view F lateral view G, H antero-lateral views. Abbreviations: a acropodite, ca cannula, cx coxa, dsp distal solenomeral process, pf prefemorite, s solenomere, sb solenomeral branch, sf seminal fossa, sg seminal groove, sph solenophore. Tip of &quot; S &quot; shaped process of sph broken. Scale bars: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1097.83916.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/674282" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4</figureCitation>
), with an additional, small, claw-like, distal solenomeral process (dsp in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="22543E8202193720A3191B3C037C0A4C" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Banatodesmus jeanneli (Tabacaru, 1980), ♂ from Pestera Haiducească de la Moldova Nouă Cave, Romania, left gonopod (NHMW MY 10257) A mesal view B antero-distal view C distal view D posterior view E anterior view F lateral view G, H antero-lateral views. Abbreviations: a acropodite, ca cannula, cx coxa, dsp distal solenomeral process, pf prefemorite, s solenomere, sb solenomeral branch, sf seminal fossa, sg seminal groove, sph solenophore. Tip of &quot; S &quot; shaped process of sph broken. Scale bars: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1097.83916.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/674282" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8CCA08376129E8FAE94342A6D4780D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
In addition, the diagnosis can be amended with the following combination of characters: medium-sized species (7-7.5 mm), 20 body rings (including telson), rings with 4-6 irregular rows of long trichoid metatergal setae, sensilla basiconica completely enclosed inside the pit of antennomere 6, hypoproct with only two long distal setae, paraprocts with only 2+2 long setae, gonopod acropodite divided into two branches, solenophore (sph in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C00E87084E9207D4D2CDAE8934518458" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Banatodesmus jeanneli (Tabacaru, 1980), ♂ from Pestera Haiducească de la Moldova Nouă Cave, Romania, left gonopod (NHMW MY 10257) A mesal view B antero-distal view C distal view D posterior view E anterior view F lateral view G, H antero-lateral views. Abbreviations: a acropodite, ca cannula, cx coxa, dsp distal solenomeral process, pf prefemorite, s solenomere, sb solenomeral branch, sf seminal fossa, sg seminal groove, sph solenophore. Tip of &quot; S &quot; shaped process of sph broken. Scale bars: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1097.83916.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/674282" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4</figureCitation>
) with three processes, of which the longest is S-shaped (broken off in the SEM image).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
